{"type":"message","id":"7930a6a4","parentId":"43f375d9","timestamp":"2026-03-28T16:22:23.996Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"localhost.run requires SSH keys to be set up. Let me try serveo.net again but in a more reliable way. Actually, let me try a different approach - use a tool like `npx serveo` or try the bore tunnel. Let me check if we can install and run bore.Actually, let me try serveo.net with a specific subdomain request, or try to set up SSH keys for localhost.run first.Actually, let me just try to set up ngrok or use another tunnel service. Let me check if we can install cloudflared or use a simple Python-based tunnel solution.\n\nWait - let me think about this differently. Maybe I can use the OpenClaw browser tool to open the dashboard for Yao Zong, since OpenClaw has browser capabilities and the server has a browser installed. \n\nBut that would just open it on the server, not help Yao Zong access it remotely. Let me try serveo again - it allocates a random subdomain each time and forwards HTTP traffic to localhost:8092. The URL format should be something like https://random.serveousercontent.com. Actually, I could also set up a simple Python web server as a reverse proxy on an already-open port like 8080, but nginx is already running there with only a default site enabled.\n\nI'm not root so I can't modify nginx configs directly. Instead, let me try running serveo.net with a persistent session in the background and provide the URL to Yao Zong. I'll create an alias in the shell profile so Yao Zong can easily restart the tunnel later if it disconnects.","thinkingSignature":"c306ac66ee66aee1862329ddc36ab3d68f6565b61725348161f33be29592441d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wwpnwos9pg1q_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Create a script to start clawpanel + tunnel for easy restart\ncat > /home/gem/.npm-global/bin/start-clawpanel.sh << 'SCRIPT'\n#!/bin/bash\n# Start ClawPanel with tunnel\nCLAWPANEL_DIR=\"/home/gem/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/@milkkey/clawpanel\"\nCLAWPANEL_PORT=${1:-8092}\nTUNNEL_PORT=${2:-80}\n\n# Kill existing processes\npkill -f \"uvicorn.*${CLAWPANEL_PORT}\" 2>/dev/null\npkill -f \"serveo.net\" 2>/dev/null\nsleep 1\n\n# Start clawpanel\ncd \"$CLAWPANEL_DIR\"\nPYTHONPATH=\"$CLAWPANEL_DIR\" python3 -c \"\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, '$CLAWPANEL_DIR')\nfrom web.app import app\nimport uvicorn\nuvicorn.run(app, host='0.0.0.0', port=${CLAWPANEL_PORT})\n\" &\n\nsleep 3\n\n# Start tunnel\nssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no -o ServerAliveInterval=60 -R 80:localhost:${CLAWPANEL_PORT} serveo.net\n\nSCRIPT\n\nchmod +x /home/gem/.npm-global/bin/start-clawpanel.sh\necho \"Script created\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":29644,"output":637,"cacheRead":57073,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87354,"cost":{"input":0.0088932,"output":0.0007643999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00171219,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.011369790000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774714929313}}
